editorialNotes.standard: Maintaining healthy habits feels a bit less daunting with a customizable self-care pet at your fingertips. With Finch, your very own companion helps you move through specific goals and guided self-care journeys. Beyond that, you can set goals, reflect, or savor a moment of mindfulness with a library of exercises and soundscapes. With consistency, you’ll uncover more about your virtual pet’s personality—and the app’s robust insights can also help you learn a lot about you and your needs too.

Take a deep breath. That phrase greets you whenever you open Calm. It’s both a call to action and a defining feature of the app’s approach to meditation: You’re going to get through this, and all you need to start is a moment. In the increasingly crowded field of apps for meditation and mindfulness, Calm stands out for its ease of use and attention to (soothing) detail.
editorialNotes.short: Try breathing techniques for quick relaxation.

editorialNotes.standard: Drift off or dial in with BetterSleep—an app that puts you in control of your soundscapes. Mix everything from crackling campfires to morning birds, or explore the app’s library of meditations, sleep tales, breath work exercises, and more.
editorialNotes.short: Listen to meditative sounds on Apple Watch.

editorialNotes.standard: Yuka can help you make informed choices about what you eat and use every day. Scan your favorite snacks or beauty products, and the app will break down any additives, irritants, nutritional red flags, and more in seconds so you know exactly what’s going into your body.
editorialNotes.short: Uncover the good and bad about your favorite foods and beauty products.

editorialNotes.standard: It’s hard to make the best even better, but the sequel to Day One lives up to expectations—and then some. The app keeps its interface streamlined but adds a wealth of new valuable features. Your journal entries contain all sorts of information—you can geolocate them, add tons of photos to each entry, and even see your day’s fitness activity. Switch over to the beautiful new photo view when you’re ready to see your world at a glance.
editorialNotes.short: Record journal entries with a tap
This all-in-one health tracker makes it easy to count your calories and plan your meals.

editorialNotes.tagline: Focus with music from St. Vincent
editorialNotes.standard: If you’re like us, you need all the help you can get turning rare quiet moments into true meditation. Headspace’s rich, accessible lessons gently explore how to improve mindfulness. Oh, and we love how Headspace’s Apple Watch app lets you hit a literal panic button when extra-stressful situations arise.
editorialNotes.short: Stay relaxed during busy times.
Bring more happiness and peace into your life with soothing music and meditation.

editorialNotes.standard: Many apps deliver soothing sounds to help you to relax, focus, or sleep. But Endel is one of the few with an algorithm smart enough to customize soundscapes for you in the moment. Sometimes it’s the sounds of the ocean, calming rain, or spherical sounds, all paired with harmonic tone sequences.
editorialNotes.short: Sound adapted to your lifestyle

editorialNotes.standard: Bookend your days with a moment of reflection in stoic., an elegantly designed journaling app made for anyone looking to carve out time for mindfulness. With insightful reflection prompts and breathing exercises, the app is filled with multiple ways to care for your mental health—with inspiration from stoic philosophy at its core.
editorialNotes.short: Meet your daily companion for journaling, meditation and reflection.

editorialNotes.standard: An invaluable tool for reaching your weight-loss goals, Lose It! tracks your meals, exercise, and nutrition. Documenting food is effortless with its built-in barcode scanner, searchable list of common grocery items, and database of popular restaurant meals’ nutritional facts. Plus, when you need some extra motivation, the app’s social features make it easy to find inspiration from friends and cheer each other on.
editorialNotes.short: Stay on track and monitor your daily calorie budget.

advisories: Infrequent/Mild Alcohol, Tobacco, or Drug Use or References
Infrequent/Mild Alcohol, Tobacco, or Drug Use or References

editorialNotes.short: Achieve your fitness and wellness goals.

editorialNotes.tagline: Join a live class from home
editorialNotes.standard: With Peloton, working out doesn’t have to happen in a silo. Whether you’re into cycling, running, rowing, or yoga, each on-demand workout class is a community affair with a leaderboard full of others cheering you on as well as themed challenges open to all. Plus, it’s easy to stay motivated thanks to the app’s encouraging coaches, and detailed stats help you stay consistent in maintaining your streak.

As its name suggests, Insight Timer started as a simple timer app for meditating. But it’s evolved into a comprehensive (and award-winning) way to help people reduce anxiety, improve their sleep, and maybe even gain a little insight along the way. It features thousands of guided meditations across a range of styles: Buddhist mindfulness (which channels your inner monk), Kundalini yoga (which focuses on your posture), walking meditation (which is meditation on the move), and many others. Lessons range from just a few minutes to long and luxurious.
editorialNotes.short: Set a timer or relax with guided meditation sessions.

advisories: Infrequent/Mild Alcohol, Tobacco, or Drug Use or References

editorialNotes.standard: When it comes to getting the most out of your sleep, a tracker that can tell you much more than how many hours you’ve snoozed goes a long way. Rise does just that. It helps you understand how your activities impact your sleep health, and it focuses on sleep debt to help you close the gap between the sleep you need and the sleep you get.
editorialNotes.short: Keep track of your night’s rest for a fresher start to your day.

name: Chair Yoga for Seniors at Home

editorialNotes.standard: Want to break a sweat? Celebrity trainers like actor Gabrielle Union and Queer Eye guru Jonathan Van Ness guide you through challenging routines you can stream on demand, while FitOn’s core fitness team leads live classes nearly every hour of the day.

We love that SmartGym creates a full-body or targeted workout based on your skill level and the equipment you have on hand. Or create your own routine by selecting an exercise (plank, overhead press) and setting the number of reps or the duration.
editorialNotes.short: Start today's workout on SmartGym.

editorialNotes.standard: There’s nothing like a cute llama to help you stay on top of your hydration goals. All you have to do? Track the liquid you consume with Waterllama. Doing so unlocks a world of characters and tools that help you monitor your overall hydration and create goals that are right for you. Timely reminders and a variety of challenges are also there to help you manage an important part of your well-being with joy.
Rather than yanking you from your slumber like an alarm clock, this app analyzes your sleep patterns using your device’s microphone, then picks your lightest sleep to rouse you gently.
editorialNotes.short: Keep track of your sleeping habits and wake up feeling rested.
Head to dreamland with bedtime stories from your wrist.

ios.subtitle: Workout, Ride and Race at Home

editorialNotes.short: Ride and run in the real world and power your avatar across our virtual worlds.

name: 天天跳绳-欢乐AI运动场
artistName: Shanghai Littlelights Education Technology Co., Ltd.

ios.subtitle: 跳绳跑步舞蹈体感切水果吃豆人

name: Clearful - Journal & Diary
artistName: Clearful Journal, Mindfulness Diary and Mental Health Inc.

editorialNotes.standard: Finding a moment to pause and reflect is made a bit more effortless with Clearful. The journaling app is full of thoughtful prompts across a variety of themes that help us find moments of gratitude, check in with our mental health, and more. The power of reflection is made even more accessible with the app’s insights and reviews, which give us a chance to understand our habits and synthesize our entries into meaningful takeaways.

ios.subtitle: Lighting to make you feel good

editorialNotes.standard: When you’re experiencing anxiety, immediate solutions can be a game changer. Rootd offers instant relief with content to help you work through a panic attack or find a moment of mindfulness. Find support through journaling, breathing exercises, visualizations, and more. Plus take a weekly anxiety questionnaire and see your average monthly results to help you track progress over time.
editorialNotes.short: Overcome panic attacks and anxiety with breathing exercises.

editorialNotes.standard: Making a pledge to get fit is easy, but finding the time to actually move our bodies is hard. Seven’s bite-size workouts don’t require a gym membership or special equipment. Best of all, we can launch these satisfying mini-routines right from Apple Watch—it’s like having a rah-rah personal trainer right on our wrist.
editorialNotes.short: There are no excuses. It’s only seven minutes a day!

editorialNotes.tagline: Quick look at your screen time
editorialNotes.standard: OffScreen is more than a screen-time tracker. With focus timers and in-depth screen-time statistics, OffScreen helps you understand your digital habits and gives you the tools to set boundaries—and see your goals through. By tracking everything from how many times you pick up your phone to how often you use it while walking, you’ll learn how to focus better on the things that matter to you.

editorialNotes.tagline: PiYo, P90X, and other intense workouts

name: Sweat: Fitness App For Women
artistName: The Bikini Body Training Company Pty Ltd

ios.subtitle: Workout At Home Or In The Gym

editorialNotes.standard: Fitness expert Kayla Itsines wants you to reach all your health and exercise goals—and her amazing app has just what you need to get there. It’s packed with everything that’s made her Bikini Body Guides an international sensation, including short 28-minute workouts (minimal equipment needed), customizable meal plans, and global fitness challenges. Plus, good news for devoted fans: Sweat also offers targeted programs designed for weights, yoga, and post-pregnancy. Kayla and her crew of awesome trainers are here to root you on.
editorialNotes.short: Try short 28-minute workouts, with a 7-day free trial.

name: Keep - 跑步健身骑行瑜伽，一键开动！

editorialNotes.standard: With detailed plans (including nutrition and cross-training advice), Runna makes an excellent, pocket-size running coach. Lean on the app’s coaches and AI-powered features to help you find your stride, connect with fellow runners, and smash your race-day goals.
